  "text": "Kafka's consumer heartbeat session timeout mechanism is distributed across client and broker components:\n\n**CLIENT SIDE (Consumer):**\n\nThe heartbeat session timeout threshold is defined in `CommonClientConfigs.SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/CommonClientConfigs.java, line 207-214). This configuration is read into `GroupRebalanceConfig.sessionTimeoutMs` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/GroupRebalanceConfig.java, line 52), which supplies the timeout value to `Heartbeat.sessionTimer` (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Heartbeat.java, line 52).\n\nDuring the consumer polling loop, the `HeartbeatThread` (a private inner class in `AbstractCoordinator.java`, line 1454) executes in its `run()` method (line 1479+). At line 1513, it calls `heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now)` to check if the session timer has expired. When true, at lines 1516-1517, it calls `markCoordinatorUnknown(\"session timed out without receiving a heartbeat response\")`, which logs the timeout event and marks the coordinator as unavailable.\n\nThe `sessionTimeoutExpired()` method in `Heartbeat.java` (lines 119-122) checks if the session timer has expired by comparing the elapsed time against the configured threshold.\n\n**BROKER SIDE (Group Coordinator):**\n\nThe broker-side session timeout thresholds are defined in `GroupCoordinatorConfig.java` (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupCoordinatorConfig.java):\n- Lines 133-141: Classic group timeout configs (`GROUP_MIN_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG`, `GROUP_MAX_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG`)\n- Lines 155-165: Consumer group timeout configs (`CONSUMER_GROUP_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG`, `CONSUMER_GROUP_MIN_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG`, `CONSUMER_GROUP_MAX_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG`)\n- Lines 222-244: Share group and streams group timeout configs\n\nIn `GroupMetadataManager.java` (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/GroupMetadataManager.java), the session timeout is scheduled using `scheduleConsumerGroupSessionTimeout()`, `scheduleShareGroupSessionTimeout()`, and similar methods (lines 4326-4482). These methods register a timer callback that executes when the session timeout expires. For classic groups, the callback invokes `expireClassicGroupMemberHeartbeat()` (lines 6664-6702), which logs messages like \"Pending member X in group Y has been removed after session timeout expiration\" or \"Member X in group Y has failed, removing it from the group.\" The timeout event key is generated by `groupSessionTimeoutKey()` (line 5988) for modern group protocols."
}

